definitions.definition: A disaccharide , C 12 H 22 O 11 formed from the digestion of starch by amylase ; is converted to glucose by maltase ; it is an isomer of trehalose

main_definition: ( biochemistry ) A disaccharide , C 12 H 22 O 11 formed from the digestion of starch by amylase ; is converted to glucose by maltase ; it is an isomer of trehalose
